<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="338" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d338">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">733.35/25a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina (<persName corresp="#p_BRW1" type="to">Bliss</persName>)</hi><note n="5" xml:id="d338fn5">The same,
                                    <hi rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, July 19, to the
                                Minister in Uruguay.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-19T17:00:00-04:00">July 19,
                                    1932—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>44. Department leaves to you and the Minister at Montevideo full
                            discretion in the matter of rendering good offices to Argentina and
                            Uruguay and Depart, will take no action except on your suggestion.</p>
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="#p_HRAHG1">Admiral Hamlet</persName>, Commandant of
                            the Coast Guard, states that vessels may remain at Montevideo if
                            necessary for a week or 10 days after their scheduled departure on July
                            20, and that the commanding officer, Commander
                                <persName>Jones</persName>, has entire discretion to comply with
                            your request to that effect.</p>
                        <p>Keep Department informed of developments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>